The paper is about face recognition systems, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses security issues, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions feature extraction approaches, which is a subfield of multimedia (cs.MM). The paper proposes a new taxonomy for face recognition systems, which involves categorization and organization, and this falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses challenges and future research directions, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG).
